In order to determine whether de novo protein synthesis is required for induction of apoptosis after CIV infection, we added cycloheximide (200 μg/ml) to CF cells 1 h prior to infection. In cells with cycloheximide, CIV infection resulted in 70% apoptotic cells as determined by blebbing assay (Fig. 7
) and 60% apoptosis as determined by TUNEL assay (Fig. 8
). Similar levels of blebbing (75%) were observed when CF cells were exposed to CIVUV after prior treatment with CHX (data not shown). CIV infections without inhibitor resulted in less than 10% apoptosis (Fig. 7, Fig. 8B). Cycloheximide alone or mock infections resulted in less than 2% blebbing. These results indicate that de novo protein synthesis is not required for apoptosis induction upon infection of CF cells with CIV.
